ODM aspirants yesterday urged the National Elections Board to ensure speedy conclusion of appeals so that those wishing to run as independents are not locked out by the Independent Electoral and Boundaries Commission. Aspirants seeking to run in August, as independent candidates, have until today to ditch their parties and get clearance from the Registrar of Political Parties and the IEBC. The commission on Tuesday gave independent aspirants until today to clear with their parties and submit their applications by Monday 8. The IEBC will publish names of all aspirants in the Kenya Gazette on May 10, according to the electoral timelines stipulated in the law.Yesterday, dozens of ODM aspirants, whose petitions were successful, said the NEB chaired by Judy Pareno is working at a snail&rsquo;s speed.